gomodel:SYNGO_663  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper is the first characterization of VGLUT3.\n\nFigure 2 shows [3H]L- glutamate uptake in intracellular membrane vesicles obtained from BON cell lysates stably expressing VGLUT3, VGLUT2 or mock vesicles.\nFigure 2a and 2b demonstrate the fraction of [3H]L- glutamate uptake that is sensitive to the H+ ionophore CCCP. CCCP-sensitive uptake is seen in VGLUT3 and VGLUT2-expressing membranes, but not in the mock membranes.\nFigure 2c demonstrates the glutamate specificity of VGLUT3.\n\nFigure 3 presents the kinetics of VGLUT2 and VGLUT3-dependent glutamate transport.. Experimental description: To analyze whether P45 represents a novel glutamate transporter, its cDNA was stably expressed in the serotoninergic endocrine cell line BON (Evers et al., 1991).\n*BON cell line is derived from a metastatic human carcinoid tumor of the pancreas." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_663" ;
